1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:19,480
We've talked about the three factors of authentication, authentication by knowledge, ownership,

2
00:00:19,480 --> 00:00:34,560
and

3
00:00:34,560 --> 00:00:41,600
We've talked about the three factors of authentication, authentication by knowledge, ownership, and characteristic.

4
00:00:41,600 --> 00:00:46,360
We can use these different factors, alone or in combination, to achieve what is often

5
00:00:46,360 --> 00:00:50,640
referred to as single or multifactor authentication.

6
00:00:50,640 --> 00:00:53,320
Let's start with single factor authentication.

7
00:00:53,320 --> 00:00:54,560
What does that mean?

8
00:00:54,560 --> 00:00:56,640
Well, at the most basic level,

9
00:00:56,640 --> 00:00:58,880
single factor authentication simply means

10
00:00:58,880 --> 00:01:02,640
that we use one of those three factors of authentication.

11
00:01:02,640 --> 00:01:05,240
So it's simply authentication by knowledge

12
00:01:05,240 --> 00:01:07,320
or authentication by ownership

13
00:01:07,320 --> 00:01:12,120
or authentication by characteristic by themselves.

14
00:01:12,120 --> 00:01:13,920
So if I were to ask you this question,

15
00:01:13,920 --> 00:01:18,360
a user logs into a system using an RSA ID token.

16
00:01:18,360 --> 00:01:19,280
What is that?

17
00:01:19,280 --> 00:01:22,160
Is that multifactor or is that single factor?

18
00:01:22,160 --> 00:01:23,720
And the answer of course is that it's

19
00:01:23,720 --> 00:01:25,800
single factor authentication

20
00:01:25,800 --> 00:01:27,320
because the only factor of authentication

21
00:01:27,320 --> 00:01:29,560
they used by just using an RSA ID key

22
00:01:29,560 --> 00:01:33,880
is authentication by ownership.

23
00:01:33,880 --> 00:01:36,640
Now, what about multifactor authentication?

24
00:01:36,640 --> 00:01:38,320
You've undoubtedly heard this term.

25
00:01:38,320 --> 00:01:40,320
It gets thrown around all of the place.

26
00:01:40,320 --> 00:01:42,680
What is the true and perfect definition

27
00:01:42,680 --> 00:01:45,320
of multifactor authentication?

28
00:01:45,320 --> 00:01:48,080
The perfect definition is that multifactor authentication

29
00:01:48,080 --> 00:01:52,520
is two or more different factors of authentication.

30
00:01:52,520 --> 00:01:55,400
And so a key to my bank is a perfect example of this.

31
00:01:55,400 --> 00:01:56,640
Just recently, they rolled out

32
00:01:56,640 --> 00:01:58,720
this whole multifactor authentication initiative

33
00:01:58,720 --> 00:01:59,960
and they were very proud of themselves

34
00:01:59,960 --> 00:02:03,440
that they now had MFA multifactor authentication.

35
00:02:03,440 --> 00:02:05,200
And what you had to do, what you have to do now,

36
00:02:05,200 --> 00:02:08,680
to log in with MFA is you have to provide first your password

37
00:02:08,680 --> 00:02:11,240
and then answer a security question.

38
00:02:11,240 --> 00:02:13,720
And is that multifactor authentication?

39
00:02:13,720 --> 00:02:16,000
Well, it's authentication by knowledge

40
00:02:16,000 --> 00:02:18,600
and then authentication by knowledge.

41
00:02:18,600 --> 00:02:21,280
Two factors, but they're the same factors.

42
00:02:21,280 --> 00:02:24,040
So that is not truly multifactor authentication.

43
00:02:24,920 --> 00:02:26,440
So that's the difference between single factor

44
00:02:26,440 --> 00:02:28,760
and multifactor authentication.

45
00:02:29,080 --> 00:02:34,560
So that means that you're not 100% integrated.

46
00:02:34,720 --> 00:02:38,080
That's what you needed.

